D. J. Bernstein writes:
|> There is no mathematical evidence for any of the following statements:
|> factoring is hard, factoring is easy, P = NP, P != NP.

pratt's demonstration that factoring is in np and in co-np is evidence
that factoring is not hard.  (in the mathematical sense.)

the oracle reductions of baker, gill, and solovay give weight to both
sides of the p =? np question.

mathematical evidence is what you make it.

	peter
